Description.
Male (
Holotype
, 
Tocantins
, 
Brazil
, IBSP 134158). Total length 5.47. Carapace 3.07 long, 2.82 wide, yellow; fovea marked. Clypeus yellow, 0.36 high. Anterior eye row straight, 0.74 wide (
Fig. 15
); posterior recurved, 1.36 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.16, ALE 0.08, PME 0.20, PLE 0.18; AME-AME 0.12, AME-ALE 0.07, PME-PME 0.24, PME-PLE 0.26, OQA 0.46, OQP 0.64, OQH 0.48. Chelicerae light brown with a patch of white bristles laterally (
Fig. 15
). Sternum whitish, bristly; 1.41 long, 1.47 wide. Labium light brown, whitish distally, 0.33 long, 0.41 wide. Legs yellow, unmarked; relative length: I- IV-II-III, I—femur 6.30/ patella-tibia 9.04/ metatarsus 6.38/ tarsus 2.66/ total 24.38; II—6.65/ 7.98/ 5.18/ 2.12/ 21.93; III—4.38/ 4.78/ 3.59/ 1.46/ 14.21; IV—6.65/ 7.58/ 5.45/ 2.39/ 22.07. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-4; II-4; III-3; IV-4. Abdomen 2.40 long, dark yellow, dorsum with several dark brown bristles anteriorly and two pairs of sigillae. Venter whitish, with scattered setae. Palpus with a bifurcated median apophysis (
Figs 111, 112
) and with a short distal tegular projection (
Fig. 111
). Ental branch of RTA elongated, with a lamellar projection at the base (
Figs 113, 114
) and the ectal branch short and distally folded (
Fig. 114
).
